Children.Text:
A population and housing census is the single most extensive, complicated and expensive statistical operation that will ever be undertaken by a statistical office. It is a snapshot or portrait of a countryâ€™s population at a particular point in time. This point in time is called Census Day, which is Monday, May 4, 2020. The census is the main source of nationwide statistics.

For the First time in the history of The Bahamas, the 2020 Census will be conducted electronically. Many Caribbean Countries are embracing this new initiative for the 2020 Round of Censuses.

You have been appointed as a Census Enumerator for the 2020 Census of Population and Housing of the Commonwealth of The Bahamas.

________________________________________
This is a very big responsibility, which has been given to you, and of great importance to the whole Commonwealth. For this reason, you are requested to perform the tasks assigned to you with the utmost care. ________________________________________

Children.Instructions:
PLEASE MARKE ALL THE BUILDINGS IN THE SAME SEQUENCE AS YOU ARE PLANNING TO ENUMERATE THEM. THIS IS IMPORTANT, AS IT HELPS YOU TO IDENTIFY THE HOUSEHOLD LATER ON FOR THE DATA COLLECTION. 
YOU CAN DO THIS EITHER AT THE BEGINNING, OR UPON ARRIVAL AT EACH BUILDING.
THE NUMBER OF POINTS PROVIDED, MUST CORRESPOND TO THE NUMBER OF BUILDINGS ENUMERATED.

TO ASSIST YOU FURTHER IN THE IDENTIFICATION, YOU ARE STILL REQUIRED TO COLLECT A SEPARATE GPS POSITION IN FRONT OF EACH BUILDING.
